## ததஅக

[ cālakkirāmam ]  
  
பெ. šālagrāma. பார். சாளக்கிராமம்  
s. a precious stone of yellowcolour held in veneration by the vaishnavas  
சாளக்கிராமம்  
s. the salagrama stone  
of a yellow or golden color; a species of ammonite  
common in the gandaka river. it is reverenced by the vaishnu vas as a representation of vishnu  
being (according to the skanda purana) pro duced from the semen which flowed as a river  
from the sexual connection of siva with vishnu in the form of a female. w. p  
921. salagrama.(c.)  
ஓரூர்  
ஓர்வகைச் சிலை